Both sides condemned the Afghan and Pakistani situation and terrorism - all forms of terrorism - and urged the convening of a UN conference.
The conclusion of the Doha trade liberalization round was also called for, although both sides bear great responsibility for its failure.
The EU confirmed that it will hold on to its energy and climate programme, i.e. by 2020 it wants to reduce polluting emissions by at least 20%.
India also agrees with this, as next year's climate conference should reach a global agreement and reduce greenhouse gas production by 50 per cent by 2050.
